g5601.definition: [Ὠβήδ] of Hebrew origin ({{h5744}}); Obed, an Israelite

g5602.definition: [ὧδε] from an adverb form of {{g3592}}; in this same spot, i.e. here or hither

g5603.definition: [ᾠδή] from {{g103}}; a chant or "ode" (the general term for any words sung; while {{g5215}} denotes especially a religious metrical composition, and {{g5568}} still more specially, a Hebrew cantillation)

g5604.definition: [ὠδίν] akin to {{g3601}}; a pang or throe, especially of childbirth

g5605.definition: [ὠδίνω] from {{g5604}}; to experience the pains of parturition (literally or figuratively)

g5606.definition: [ὦμος] perhaps from the alternate of {{g5342}}; the shoulder (as that on which burdens are borne)

g5607.definition: [ὤν] ,     including the feminine      οὖσα; and the neuter      ὄνpresent participle of {{g1510}}; being

g5608.definition: [ὠνέομαι] middle voice from an apparently primary ὦνος (a sum or price); to purchase (synonymous with the earlier {{g4092}})

g5610.definition: [ὥρα] apparently a primary word; an "hour" (literally or figuratively)

g5611.definition: [ὡραῖος] from {{g5610}}; belonging to the right hour or season (timely), i.e. (by implication) flourishing (beauteous (figuratively))

g5612.definition: [ὠρύομαι] middle voice of an apparently primary verb; to "roar"

g5613.definition: [ὡς] probably adverb of comparative from {{g3739}}; which how, i.e. in that manner (very variously used, as follows)

g5614.definition: [ὡσαννά] of Hebrew origin ({{h3467}} and {{h4994}}); oh save!; hosanna (i.e. hoshia-na), an exclamation of adoration

g5615.definition: [ὡσαύτως] from {{g5613}} and an adverb from {{g846}}; as thus, i.e. in the same way

g5617.definition: [Ὡσηέ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1954}}); Hosee (i.e. Hoshea), an Israelite

g5618.definition: [ὥσπερ] from {{g5613}} and {{g4007}}; just as, i.e. exactly like

g5619.definition: [ὡσπερεί] from {{g5618}} and {{g1487}}; just as if, i.e. as it were

g5620.definition: [ὥστε] from {{g5613}} and {{g5037}}; so too, i.e. thus therefore (in various relations of consecution, as follow)

g5621.definition: [ὠτίον] diminutive of {{g3775}}; an earlet, i.e. one of the ears, or perhaps the lobe of the ear

g5622.definition: [ὠφέλεια] from a derivative of the base of {{g5624}}; usefulness, i.e. benefit

g5623.definition: [ὠφελέω] from the same as {{g5622}}; to be useful, i.e. to benefit

g5624.definition: [ὠφέλιμος] from a form of {{g3786}}; helpful or serviceable, i.e. advantageous
